Cricket World Cup Will Cut 4 Teams, Feature 10 Squads in 2015, Lorgat Says

-- B y   A n o o p   A g r a w a l
-- 
2011-04-04T13:36:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/cricket-world-cup-will-cut-4-teams-feature-10-squads-in-2015-lorgat-says.html
The 2015 Cricket  World Cup  will
feature 10 teams after tournament organizers decided to trim
four nations from the event, International Cricket Council Chief
Executive Haroon Lorgat told reporters in Mumbai today.  The 2011 tournament, won by co-host  India  two days ago,
featured 14 teams and lasted six weeks, prompting criticism that
it was too long.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anoop Agrawal in Mumbai at 
 aagrawal8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
